               <head>Work on Sufism</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_978-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled lengthy treatise by an unnamed author on the principles of Sufism and the magical significance of letters, attributed at the end to <persName key="viaf_65292796" role="att">Khvājah Muḥammad Pārsā</persName> (d. 822/1420). The work is endorsed as the <title>Taḥqīqāt</title>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 304v): completed by <persName key="person_f7332" role="scr">Muḥammad Afz̤al Khān</persName> for <persName key="person_f7339" role="pat">Muḥammad Ashraf ṣāḥib</persName>, morning of Thursday, 19 Jumādá al-S̲ānī year 27 of Emperor <persName key="viaf_45680638" role="oth">Muḥammad Shāh</persName>’s reign (1158/19 July 1745). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Unbound; disintegrated outer leather matter of binding, lacking internal boards; wormholes; fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
